%h4 Welcome to #{service_name}!
.welcome_text
  %p
    Pitskun #{service_name} is meant for all the people living in the Pitäjänmäki discrict: Reimarlan, Marttilan, Strömbergin, Taimiston and Pitäjänmäki industrial district / Piimäki. Add your info to #{service_name} and tell what you need and how you could help others out by, for example, lending or renting your goods or offering your help.
  %p
    After you contact a person in #{service_name}, it's usually good to agree on a place to meet. Good public places for this purpose in Pitäjänmäki include the premises of Valintatalo, Church, Library or S-market. The users of the service should always assess the trustworthiness of the other party before meeting, and having the first meeting in a public place can be the most care-free option for everyone. Also remember to give feedback to each other after helping each other out, so you can build your reputation as a trustworthy person in the #{service_name} community.
  %p
    Pitskun #{service_name} is a part of the "From Neighborhoods to Village Communities" project which aims to make neighborhoods more lively and offer residents a chance to participate in developing the environment they live in. The project is a part of World Design Capital Helsinki 2012 and Helsinki 200 years as capital -projects. The project is executed by Sharetibe Ltd and it is funded by Helsinki Communications Office, Helsinki 200 years as capital -project and Forum Virium Helsinki. The service will remain in residents' use also after year 2012.
